Practice DescriptionMr. Sands focuses his practice on trials involving complex business litigation matters, including:•Toxic Torts •Product Liability •Commercial Litigation •Personal Injury Litigation •Cybersecurity Mr. Sands has tried cases in both state and federal courts and has represented clients in Illinois, Missouri, California and numerous federal courts throughout the country on behalf of defendants in multi-million dollar litigation, including toxic tort, product liability, transportation, admiralty, class actions, drug and medical device, personal injury, premises liability, medical malpractice, insurance coverage, and bad faith litigation.Mr. Sands serves as regional and statewide counsel for several manufacturer defendants who are named in toxic tort litigation throughout the country, provides litigation management, oversight and coordination in thousands of cases for several Fortune 500 clients, and has served as the lead settlement negotiator for cases pending in 14 states for multiple toxic tort clients. Law School Honors/Involvement•American Jurisprudence Award, Civil Trial Advocacy •Phi Delta Phi Legal Honor Society Awards & Distinctions•Recipient, Ingersoll Rand Company Legal Eagle Award (2013) •Illinois Super Lawyer (2013-2017) •AV Preeminent Attorneys by Martindale-Hubbell •Illinois Leading Lawyers Network (since 2014) •Personal Injury Defense: General •Products Liability Defense •Transportation Defense •Toxic Tort Defense Legal Lectures/Presentations•“Proving and Disproving Damages in Personal Injury Cases,” Illinois Institute for Continuing Legal Education, Chicago IL (2008) •“Recent Developments in Asbestos Litigation,” Illinois Manufacturers Association Video Reference Library (2016)•“Asbestos Litigation Trends in Cook County,” Harris Martin Midwest Asbestos Litigation Conference (2015)• Social Media - Discovery, Use and Admissibility at Trial,” HeplerBroom University (2013)•“Best Practices in Asbestos Litigation,” Ingersoll Rand Company (2013) Community Involvement•Illinois Junior Academy of Science Regional Competition Judge (Physics) •Young Hearts for Life, Volunteer ECG provider
